%N A396365 Decimal expansion of the alpha constant in the SELU activation function.
%C A396365 SELU(x) = scale*(max(0,x)+min(0,alpha*(exp(x)-1))).
%C A396365 SELU is an activation function derived from ELU (Exponential Linear Unit), which uses the identity function for x >= 0 and exp(x)-1 for x <= 0.
%C A396365 It multiplies the negative-region output of ELU by the constant alpha and additionally scales the entire function by the constant lambda so that the outputs of a neural network converge toward zero mean and unit variance.
%H A396365 Günter Klambauer, Thomas Unterthiner, Andreas Mayr, and Sepp Hochreiter, <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/1706.02515">Self-Normalizing Neural Networks</a>, arXiv:1706.02515 [cs.LG], 2017.
%F A396365 Equals sqrt(2/Pi)/(1 - exp(1/2)*erfc(1/sqrt(2))).
%e A396365 1.6732632423543772848170429916716...
%t A396365 RealDigits[Sqrt[2/Pi]/(1 - Exp[1/2] * Erfc[1/Sqrt[2]]), 10, 105][[1]] (* _Amiram Eldar_, May 24 2026 *)
%o A396365 (PARI) alpha = sqrt(2/Pi) / (1 - exp(1/2) * erfc(1/sqrt(2.0)))
